<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-22T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-22T22:36:00-05:00" n="1081" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1081">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3685.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-22T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mr. de la Barra to-day indicated in conversation the opinion that the
                            present Government could not continue to exist, though personally he
                            hoped it might. I advised him to use the utmost diligence in supporting
                            the present Government to the point where it was apparent it could not
                            live and then to use his influence with Congress.</p>
                        <p>Conditions in Morelos, Guerrero, Sinaloa, and Puebla growing worse.
                            Bodies of revolutionists of from 100 to 300 in different groups have
                            practically surrounded Mexico City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>